## About

By default recurring meetings in outlook has a “end date”. This document provides the instructions to create a meeting without a end date.

### Instructions

Open the calendar view in outlook, then click new meeting.  
On the meeting screen click “make recurring”
![Pasted image 20221124105457.png](data:image/png;base64,)
![](blob:https://neonomics.atlassian.net/31882b93-64fd-4718-841c-a51aafd18e56#media-blob-url=true&id=1f189659-b938-4ea4-96f0-8557d7e1050b&collection=contentId-2811330575&contextId=2811330575&mimeType=image%2Fpng&name=image-20210413-100036.png&size=30943&height=419&width=619&alt=)

In the pop-up select “no end date”
![Pasted image 20221124105509.png](data:image/png;base64,)
![](blob:https://neonomics.atlassian.net/676e00d9-29b9-479d-9e40-11efb6d5e90f#media-blob-url=true&id=561c9fc9-a3cc-4994-addd-0c446d25ec0f&collection=contentId-2811330575&contextId=2811330575&mimeType=image%2Fpng&name=image-20210413-100106.png&size=20356&height=402&width=483&alt=)

Note! This only applies to meetings booked without a room. When booking with a room in the office a limit of 180 days is enforced to avoid “stale” meetings eating up all the available time.
